==English==

===Etymology===
From the term {{m|en|20/20}} referring to normal [[visual]] [[acuity]].

===Proverb===
{{head|en|proverb|head=[[hindsight]] [[is]] [[20/20]]}}

# {{context|idiomatic|lang=en}} In [[hindsight]] things are [[obvious]] that were not obvious from the [[outset]]; one is able to [[evaluate]] past [[choice]]s more [[clearly]] than at the time of the choice.

